                </p>
                <details>
                    <summary class="sum2">
                      Chapter 1: Total Framework of the Toyota Production
                      System
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                      This chapter primarily focuses on various important
                      aspects on which total framework of the toyoto
                      production systems lies on.  The topics it highlights
                      are primary purpose, kanban systems, production
                      smoothing, shortening setup time, process layout for
                      shortened lead times and one-piece production,
                      standardization of operations, autonomation, improvement
                      activities, the Goal of TPS. <br>

                      The author describes about each topic in much detail and
                      in great depth.  He talks about how did toyoto achieved
                      its primary goal of profit through cost reduction by
                      employing good strategies like elimination of
                      overproduction, limiting excess inventory and
                      overproduction, reducing unncessary capital
                      investments. <br>

                      Quantity control, quality assurance, respect for
                      umanity are other important points in the framework of
                      toyoto production systems.  To achieve continous flow in
                      the production, Just-in-Time and automation were
                      introduced.  Other important systems like kanban systems
                      were introduced to complement the goals of toyoto
                      production systems but kanban systems do not make up the
                      complete framework. <br>

                      You can visit this link for more information regarding
                      Kanban systesm: <a href="https://gcallah.github.io/DevOps/workflow/kanban.html">Link</a> <br>

                      <figure>
                          <img
                          src="../reviews/img/kanban_system.png"
                          width="403" height="304">
                          <figcaption>
                             Kanban System (page 10)
                          </figcaption>
                      </figure>
                      <p>
                        Another important point was discussed in this chapter
                        relating to the production of the toyoto production
                        systems.  They could eleminate unnecessary inventories
                        and capital investments by employing methods like
                        production smoothing which stated that there should
                        be a production of item when it is able to sell enough
                        in the market or when the market demands that
                        particular product for that day.  <br>
                      </p>

