                <details>
                    <summary class="sum2">
                      Chapter 2 Implementation Steps for the Toyota Production
                      System
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                      This chapter discusses all the important steps regarding
                      a JIT process and also gives a case study about
                      introduction of JIT at Toyo aluminum.  <br>
                      Steps given in the book (on page 25) are: <br>
                      1. Upper Management Plays a Key Role <br>
                      2. Establish a Project Team <br>
                      3. Prepare an Implementation Schedule and Set Goals to
                      Be Achieved within the Schedule <br>
                      4. Introduce a Pilot Project  <br>
                      5. Move from a Downstream Process to an Upstream Process <br> <br>

                      The JIT process starts off with the upper management
                      which makes the crucial decisions regarding the
                      production design, plan and allotmenet of resources for
                      the lower employess.  This step is followed by
                      establishing a JIT team which overlooks all the processes
                      related to the JIT process, this team consists of
                      sectional and sub-sectional managers.  These managers
                      make up plans which needs to be followed by other
                      employees to meed the deadlines then implement the last
                      step to move a downstream process to an upstream
                      process. <br> <br>

                      This chapter also introduces other important concepts
                      which can be used to implement JIT like 5S concept
                      (Seiri (arrangement), Seiton (tidiness), Seiso (cleaning)
                      , Seiketsu (cleanliness), and Shitsuke (training)),
                      one-piece-production, automation, kanban cards systems. <br>

                      The other part of this chapter deals about a case study
                      about introduction of JIT at Toyo Aluminum.  It talk
                      about how they followed all the steps which are listed
                      above.  There campaigns included "JUMP 60" & "GO GO
                      Campaign".

