                    </p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary class="sum2">
                      Chapter 3: Adaptable Kanban System Maintains Just-In-Time
                       Production
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                      This chapter discusses about how kanban systems where
                      implemented within Toyota Production System to implement
                      JIT.  As previously stated that kanban systems on a
                      whole don't make up the toyoto production systems but
                      kanban systems just complement the JIT. The author
                      defines the pull system as "The subsequent process of
                      withdrawing the parts from the preceding process". The
                      author subsequently explains that final assembly line
                      pulls the necessary products as they know the exact
                      quantity of parts required and then subsequent processes
                      utilize them. <br> <br>

                      The author talks about various types of kanbans like
                      withdrawal kanban and production-ordering kanban.
                      </p>

                      <figure>
                          <img
                          src="../reviews/img/kanban_types.png" width="430"
                          height="430">
                          <figcaption>
                              Main Types of Kanban Systems (page 41)
                          </figcaption>
                      </figure>

                    <p>
                      The author talks about how a kanban can be implemented
                      effectively in JIT process of a toyoto production
                      systems by stating few rules and talking about why
                      those rules are important for JIT. (These rules are
                      very specific to the toyoto production systems).  The
                      rest of the chapter author talks about various kanban
                      systems like express kanban, emergency kanban, job-order
                      kanban, through kanban, common kanban, card or truck as
                      kanban.
                    </p>
